	(663,1,'Science on the surface of a comet','http://www.esa.int/Our_Activities/Space_Science/Rosetta/Science_on_the_surface_of_a_comet','\n								<img src=\"http://www.esa.int/var/esa/storage/images/esa_multimedia/images/2015/07/descending_to_a_comet/15539515-5-eng-GB/Descending_to_a_comet_small.gif\" width=\"1019\" height=\"573\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"8\" /><br />\n		<p>\nComplex molecules that could be key building blocks of life, the daily rise and fall of temperature, and an assessment of the surface properties and internal structure of the comet are just some of the highlights of the first scientific analysis of the data returned by Rosetta?s lander Philae last November. &nbsp;\n</p>\n	',0,'1438279200',NULL,'2015-08-07 17:17:06','2015-08-07 17:17:06'),
